15/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Ruling coalition partners decided on Monday (14 July) to establish a panel to monitor implementation of the new amnesty law. It will include representatives of the political parties, as well as members of the international community. The decision to establish the panel followed the recent detention of several members of the Albanian National Liberation Army.
In other news, Luxemburg has ratified Macedonia's EU Stabilisation and Association Agreement. So far, 12 of the 15 EU members have backed the agreement, which is crucial to opening EU entry talks further down the road. (A1 TV, MIA - 14/07/03)
